This paper is primarily focused on language emergence and learning in neural agents, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of cultural and genetic evolution in the learning process, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation metrics used in the paper are related to the performance of the agents, which can be considered as a subfield of neural networks (cs.NE) and software engineering (cs.SD).
